<TITLE> Sri Lanka says 6 rebel boats sunk in sea battle </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Colombo, Dec 26 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Sri Lanka's Navy battled a flotilla of Tamil Tiger boats off the island's northwest tip on Wednesday, sinking 6 rebel vessels including two suicide boats, the military said. "They were involved in arms smuggling," said military spokesman Brigadier Udaya Nanayakkara. "Altogether 16 Tiger boats were observed. The navy destroyed four boats, and two suicide boats rammed a navy fast attack craft, which was badly damaged." It was not immediately clear how many people were killed in the clash, the latest in a series of land and sea battles amid renewed civil war. There were no independent accounts of what had happened and the Tigers were not immediately available for comment
